  <div style="background:#1a1a1a;border:1px solid #f90;border-radius:6px;padding:1rem;margin-bottom:1rem">
    <div style="color:#f90;font-size:0.9rem;margin-bottom:8px">6-Stage Decoding Pipeline</div>
    <pre style="margin:0;color:#ccc;white-space:pre-wrap;font-size:0.85rem;line-height:1.5">
Stage 1: Browser URL Decoding
  Browser auto-decodes most percent-encoded chars
  Exception: %2f stays as %2f in pathname
      ↓
Stage 2: HistoryLocation.getURL()
  Strips baseURL/rootURL prefixes
  No additional decoding
      ↓
Stage 3: route-recognizer.recognize()
  Strips hash and query string
  Calls normalizePath() if ENCODE_AND_DECODE_PATH_SEGMENTS=true
      ↓
Stage 3a: normalizePath()
  Split on /, for each segment:
    decodeURIComponent(segment)
    .replace(/%|\//g, encodeURIComponent)
  Dots decode: %2e%2e → ..
  Slashes re-encode: / → %2F
      ↓
Stage 4: State Machine Matching
  :param → regex ([^/]+) — rejects literal /
  *param → regex (.+) — accepts everything
      ↓
Stage 5: findHandler()
  :param → decodeURIComponent(capture)  ← THE KEY DECODE
  *param → raw capture (no decode)       ← SKIPPED!
      ↓
Stage 6: model(params)
  Developer receives:
    :param → fully decoded (%2F → /)
    *param → normalized but not final-decoded (%2F preserved)</pre>
  </div>

